  "body": "When using $INCLUDE in a zone file, CoreDNS fails to start up with this message:\r\n\r\n```2017/08/10 12:49:15 middleware/file: zone.mydomain.com: dns: failed to open `\r\n': \"\\n\" at line: 46:22```\r\n\r\nThe zonefile looks like this:\r\n\r\n```$TTL 5m\r\n\r\nmydomain.com.     IN      SOA     dns.yourdomain.com. postmaster.yourdomain.com. (\r\n                        2017081001\r\n                        14400\r\n                        7200\r\n                        604800\r\n                        3600 )\r\n\r\n<omitted>\r\n\r\n$INCLUDE zone.mydomain.com-include\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe file zone.mydomain.com-include exists in the CoreDNS startup directory which is the same folder the zonefiles reside in. Putting an absolute path doesn't change anything. Judging from the error message, maybe a parse error?",
